    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-11-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-11-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="465"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d465">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">814.24/372</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The American Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Des Portes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Guatemalan Minister for Foreign
                        Affairs</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Salazar</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="26" xml:id="d465fn26">Copy transmitted to the Department by
                        the Minister in Guatemala in his despatch No. 3378, November 17; received
                        November 20.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 338</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-11-16">November 16,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to inform Your Excellency
                    that I have received a communication from the Department of State in <pb
                        facs="0465" n="451" xml:id="pg_451"/> Washington, D.C., informing me that
                    the full powers authorizing me to sign the Lend-Lease Agreement and the
                    accompanying Note and Memorandum of Agreement have been signed by the President
                    of the United States of America and are being transmitted to me by air mail.</p>
                <p>Pending the receipt of the full powers, which will of course be delivered
                    promptly to Your Excellency, it is requested that this communication be accepted
                    in lieu thereof for the purpose of the signature on this date of the Lend-Lease
                    Agreement and accompanying documents.</p>
                <p>Please accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fay Allen Des Portes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
